WEBVTT

00:04.681 --> 00:07.165
So, you finished <i>90 Dances, 90 Nations</i>
huh?

00:07.190 --> 00:08.278
Um... ***

00:08.297 --> 00:09.968
My dad's new girlfriend
is quite the offer.

00:10.005 --> 00:11.300
Yeah, I love it.

00:11.702 --> 00:12.766
How did you...
I don't know...

00:12.791 --> 00:14.830
summarize the character
to the plot?

00:14.855 --> 00:16.094
You haven't read it, have you?

00:16.097 --> 00:17.530
(sighs) It's 800 pages

00:17.532 --> 00:18.864
of a woman recovering
from her divorce

00:18.866 --> 00:20.099
by dancing around the globe.

00:20.101 --> 00:21.567
Could you just give me
the CliffsNotes, please?

00:21.569 --> 00:23.035
My dad's bringing her by
after lunch.

00:23.037 --> 00:25.705
Well, it was subtle
with its complex narrative

00:25.707 --> 00:28.207
- and thematic prose.
- You didn't read it either.

00:28.209 --> 00:29.508
It is 800 pages.

00:29.510 --> 00:31.043
I've been trying to download
the audio book

00:31.045 --> 00:32.211
for the last 12 hours.

00:32.213 --> 00:33.546
ANDREW: Oh, hey, I cannot
thank you guys enough

00:33.548 --> 00:35.614
for turning me on
to Lily's book.

00:35.616 --> 00:36.916
I mean, I may not be

00:36.918 --> 00:38.584
a middle-aged divorcée,

00:38.586 --> 00:40.519
but color me swept away.

00:40.521 --> 00:42.188
Yeah, and all the dancing.

00:42.190 --> 00:43.622
Dancing.

00:43.624 --> 00:44.924
Dancing? There was no dancing.

00:44.926 --> 00:46.158
The dancing was a metaphor

00:46.160 --> 00:47.993
for her emotional catharsis.

00:47.995 --> 00:49.828
Paco the farm boy makes that
very clear in chapter 6.

00:49.830 --> 00:51.230
You didn't read it.

00:51.232 --> 00:53.199
Yeah, I didn't either.
You know me.

00:53.201 --> 00:55.267
I drift reading the back
of a mac and cheese box.

00:55.269 --> 00:57.403
So, how is it going
with Lily and your dad?

00:57.405 --> 00:58.737
Um, pretty well, I think.

00:58.739 --> 00:59.905
I mean, you know, he's cautious.

00:59.907 --> 01:01.707
He likes to take things
nice and slow.

01:01.709 --> 01:03.642
(elevator bell dings)

01:03.644 --> 01:04.977
Or slutty and quick.

01:06.913 --> 01:07.946
(clears throat) Dad?

01:07.948 --> 01:09.314
(gasps) Oh!

01:09.316 --> 01:10.549
Hey, gang.

01:10.551 --> 01:13.185
May I present
Ms. Lily Schecter,

01:13.187 --> 01:15.954
the author of
<i>90 Dances, 90 Nations.</i>

01:15.956 --> 01:17.389
And I was worried
that meeting all of you

01:17.391 --> 01:18.457
might be awkward.

01:18.459 --> 01:19.491
(laughter)

01:19.493 --> 01:20.792
So you must be Sydney.

01:20.794 --> 01:22.094
I can tell

01:22.096 --> 01:23.428
because you look
the most horrified.

01:23.430 --> 01:25.597
Uh, no, no, we're just
real excited to meet you.

01:25.599 --> 01:27.032
- We loved your book.
- Couldn't put it down.

01:27.034 --> 01:28.433
- Read it in a night.
- I actually read it.

01:28.435 --> 01:30.569
Oh, how kind.
Did you have a favorite part?

01:30.571 --> 01:32.638
- Yes I did, because I actually read it.
- Chapter 12.

01:32.640 --> 01:34.706
Chen-Lu with the...
the Sea of Japan was...

01:34.708 --> 01:35.941
Oh, so you're all liars.

01:35.943 --> 01:37.342
It's okay.

01:37.344 --> 01:38.377
I forgive you.

01:38.379 --> 01:39.811
Well, I promise,

01:39.813 --> 01:42.547
<i>90 Dances, 90 Nations</i> is
at the top of my must-read list

01:42.549 --> 01:44.549
once I stop being a workaholic.

01:44.551 --> 01:46.618
Oh, Sydney, if I could give you
one piece of advice

01:46.620 --> 01:48.286
that I've learned
on all of my life travels,

01:48.288 --> 01:50.422
it's that you have got
to slow down a little bit.

01:50.424 --> 01:52.424
You need to cut out
some time for yourself.

01:52.426 --> 01:54.226
You know,
just take a breath and...

01:54.228 --> 01:55.794
(gasps) Balls!

01:55.796 --> 01:57.262
I've got a meeting
in 15 minutes.

01:57.264 --> 01:59.865
It's at a women's shelter.

01:59.867 --> 02:00.932
I mean, it's kind of a bummer

02:00.934 --> 02:02.434
because none of them
can afford my book.

02:02.436 --> 02:03.668
That was so mean.

02:03.670 --> 02:04.903
I'm really a nice person.

02:04.905 --> 02:06.805
So we're on for Thursday?
Absolutely.

02:06.807 --> 02:08.573
It's a date. No...

02:08.574 --> 02:10.008
An adventure.

02:11.243 --> 02:13.712
(hisses)

02:13.714 --> 02:15.413
So, what's the big plan
for the date on Thursday?

02:15.415 --> 02:16.481
Nothing too fancy.

02:16.483 --> 02:17.882
Only the greatest
night of romance

02:17.884 --> 02:19.150
anyone ever had.

02:19.152 --> 02:20.685
And of course,
a magical ending.

02:20.687 --> 02:22.187
Oh, I wouldn't put
that much pressure

02:22.189 --> 02:23.588
on yourself.

02:23.590 --> 02:24.923
The first time's
not always magical.

02:24.925 --> 02:26.391
Sometimes it's over
really quick,

02:26.393 --> 02:28.293
but then you don't have
to retake geometry.

02:28.295 --> 02:30.094
Oh, there's a lot of story
in that little sentence.

02:30.096 --> 02:32.664
(man sobbing) Does anyone
else hear someone crying?

02:32.666 --> 02:33.865
Yeah, I'd know
those ugly wails anywhere.

02:33.867 --> 02:35.233
That's Gordon.

02:38.404 --> 02:40.104
Gordon, is that you cr...

02:40.106 --> 02:41.773
Oh! (grunts)

02:41.775 --> 02:44.008
(groans) Timothy kicked me out.

02:44.010 --> 02:45.877
My marriage is over.

02:45.879 --> 02:47.845
Ow! That really hurt.

02:48.947 --> 02:51.582
♪ Oh, oh, oh, oh, oh, oh ♪

02:51.584 --> 02:54.452
♪ Oh, oh, oh, oh, oh, oh ♪

02:54.454 --> 02:57.388
♪ Oh, oh, oh, oh, oh, oh ♪

02:57.390 --> 03:00.224
♪ Oh, oh-oh-oh-oh-oh ♪

03:00.226 --> 03:01.526
♪ Oh, oh, oh ♪

03:01.528 --> 03:03.002
♪ Oh, oh, oh, oh. ♪

03:03.027 --> 03:05.986
